<P>Lady Bla&s;t left her pool, unfini&s;hed, to
the care of a friend, on purpo&s;e to have the
<PB N="214" REF="215">
&s;atisfaction of &s;eeing where Lord Melvile
&s;topped.</P>
<P>She had the tran&s;cendent happine&s;s, as
